nd%20and%20I%20married%20in%202008%2C%20we%20made%20a%20big%20mistake.%20Though%20at%20the%20time%2C%20it%20felt%20like%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-think-many-people-better-off-renting-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Egood%20investment%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20bid%20adieu%20to%20our%20beloved%20two-bedroom%20Astoria%2C%20Queens%20rental%20and%20bought%20an%20apartment%20seven%20miles%20southeast%20in%20Forest%20Hills.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInitially%2C%20we%20wanted%20to%20stay%20in%20Astoria%2C%20where%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frich-people-new-york-city-helicopter-commute-avoid-cars-traffic-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecommute%20into%20Manhattan%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20just%2030%20minutes%2C%20and%20we%20could%20walk%20to%20a%20restaurant%20with%20a%20different%20global%20cuisine%20every%20weekend%20for%20months%20without%20repeating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20a%20one-bedroom%20apartment%2C%20a%20third%20smaller%20than%20our%20rental%2C%20cost%20an%20average%20of%20%24425%2C000%20in%20Astoria%2C%20and%20we%20didn't%20think%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhome-sellers-summer-disappointment-mortgage-rates-house-prices-real-estate-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20price%20was%20right%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20so%20we%20looked%20elsewhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20losing%20a%20bidding%20war%20for%20a%20place%20on%20Austin%20Street%2C%20we%20were%20running%20out%20of%20hope.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20when%20a%20seller%20quickly%20accepted%20our%20bid%20of%20%24250%2C000%E2%80%94%2425%2C000%20under%20asking%20price%E2%80%94for%20a%20spacious%20apartment%20within%20a%20meticulously%20maintained%20elevator%20building%20complex%20in%20Forest%20Hills%2C%20we%20were%20thrilled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20should've%20realized%20something%20was%20amiss.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2268d9eae4-1b4b-4b79-a992-6e1b87b738df%5C%22%3EWe%20missed%20a%20big%20red%20flag%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224608%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20group%20of%20eight%20people%20sitting%20in%20a%20living%20room%20watching%20tv%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6882430df748d8c055f632e9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223072%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBodgas%20with%20husband%20and%20friends%20in%20their%20Astoria%20apartment.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Meredith%20Bodgas%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHad%20we%20done%20more%20research%2C%20we%20would've%20seen%20that%20even%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-housing-supply-outlook-mortgage-rates-inventory-prices-redfin-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebelow-asking%20price%3C%2Fa%3E%20we%20offered%20was%20more%20than%20any%20one-bedroom%20apartment%20in%20the%20whole%20seven-building%20complex%20had%20ever%20sold%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20we%20were%20distracted%20by%20the%20sprawling%20courtyard%20dotted%20with%20fountains%20and%20flowers%20that%20resembled%20an%20English%20garden.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20also%20loved%20the%20convenience%20of%20a%20supermarket%20across%20the%20street%20and%20a%20subway%20stop%20on%20the%20corner.%20Plus%2C%20with%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiny-apartments-in-new-york-city-2016-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E1%2C000%20square%20feet%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20we%20had%20plenty%20of%20space%20to%20host%20friends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%20of%20purchase%2C%20we%20didn't%20mind%20the%20dearth%20of%20nearby%20restaurants%20or%20that%20our%20commutes%20would%20be%20about%2015%20minutes%20longer.%20These%20were%20small%20sacrifices%20for%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftop-benefit-of-investing-in-real-estate-leveraged-appreciation-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebenefit%20of%20owning%20property%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20we%20thought.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20missed%20a%20major%20red%20flag%2C%20though.%20The%20apartment%20was%20between%20the%20trash%20compactor%20and%20the%20elevator.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeing%20next%20to%20just%20one%20and%20either%20dealing%20with%20the%20smell%20and%20propensity%20for%20roaches%20from%20the%20trash%20compactor%20or%20the%20noise%20from%20the%20elevator%20is%20bad%20enough.%20Being%20wedged%20between%20both%20made%20the%20particular%20string%20of%20apartments%20we%20were%20in%E2%80%94the%20K%20line%E2%80%94the%20least%20desirable%20in%20the%20whole%20building.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e2903b79-4a5d-4552-9f88-23e3b8af49da%5C%22%3EThe%20apartment%20wasn't%20what%20we'd%20hoped%20for%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225760%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22busy%20street%20in%20new%20york%20city%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6882461285e81483682e995e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223840%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20busy%20street%20in%20New%20York%20City.%3Cp%3Ebatuhanozdel%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20quickly%20discovered%20that%20the%20elevator%20was%20out%20of%20service%20so%20often%20that%20we%20might%20as%20well%20have%20moved%20into%20a%20walk-up.%20Thankfully%2C%20we%20were%20on%20the%20third%20floor%2C%20so%20it%20wasn't%20a%20huge%20hike%2C%20but%20it%20was%20still%20an%20annoyance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20we%20bought%2C%20we%20knew%20the%20building%20was%20close%20to%20Queens%20Blvd.%2C%20one%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopen-streets-new-york-city-increased-spending-businesses-fifth-avenue-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebusiest%20streets%20in%20New%20York%20City%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20we%20thought%20it%20wouldn't%20be%20so%20loud%20because%20we%20didn't%20face%20it%20directly.%20That%20was%20a%20mistake.%20We%20had%20to%20use%20a%20fan%20and%20a%20white%20noise%20machine%20to%20mute%20the%20sounds%20of%20sirens%20blaring%20throughout%20the%20night.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20few%20short%20months%20after%20moving%20in%2C%20our%20maintenance%20fee%2C%20which%20we%20paid%20in%20addition%20to%20our%20mortgage%2C%20instantly%20rose%20by%20%24100%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlus%2C%20the%20same%20model%20apartment%20in%20our%20building%E2%80%94not%20even%20on%20our%20crappy%20K%20line%E2%80%94sold%20for%20under%20%24200%2C000.%20We%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frealtors-real-estate-agent-commission-home-housing-sales-ripoff-cost-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efelt%20ripped%20off%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c30efc59-177e-426f-affd-111255d25a78%5C%22%3EOur%20neighbors%20didn't%20help%20the%20situation%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fairness%2C%20our%20large%20apartment%20made%20us%20the%20natural%20party%20spot%2C%20and%20we%20had%20a%20blast%20playing%20Rock%20Band%20and%20Wii%20Sports%20with%20all%20our%20friends%20(remember%2C%20this%20was%20the%20late%20aughts%20and%20early%202010s).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20cranky%20older%20woman%20below%20us%20would%20send%20her%20boyfriend%20to%20yell%20at%20us%2C%20though%20twice%20he%20invited%20himself%20in%20and%20even%20played%20on%20the%20drumset.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20upstairs%20neighbor%20was%20even%20worse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20day%2C%20water%20began%20raining%20down%20into%20our%20apartment%20and%20collapsed%20our%20kitchen%20ceiling%2C%20destroying%20some%20of%20our%20cabinets.%20We're%20not%20clear%20exactly%20what%20happened%2C%20but%20we%20suspect%20that%20our%20upstairs%20neighbor%20had%20forgotten%20to%20turn%20off%20the%20kitchen%20sink.%20We%20never%20got%20an%20explanation%20or%20apology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20assumed%20our%20higher%20maintenance%20fees%20would%20go%20toward%20fixing%20the%20damage.%20However%2C%20the%20maintenance%20folks%20told%20us%20those%20repairs%20went%20beyond%20the%20building's%20responsibility%2C%20so%20we%20spent%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20out%20of%20pocket%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22