udd%20Antin%20has%20held%20leadership%20roles%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finfluence-c-suite-execs-career-strategies-2025-4%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMeta%20and%20Airbnb%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20he%20worked%20between%202012%20and%202022.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDuring%20that%20time%2C%20he%20led%20teams%20through%20rapid%20changes%2C%20such%20as%20layoffs.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20learned%20one%20secret%20to%20effective%20leadership%3A%20authentic%20clarity.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20course%20of%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsoftware-engineer-tips-big-tech-roles-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecareer%20in%20Big%20Tech%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I've%20been%20lucky%20to%20work%20at%20several%20successful%2C%20fast-growing%20companies.%20At%20Meta%20and%20Airbnb%2C%20I%20helped%20scale%20research%20and%20design%20teams%20from%202012%20to%202022%2C%20ultimately%20becoming%20Head%20of%20Design%20Studio%20at%20Airbnb.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20loved%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-build-engaged-high-performing-teams%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebuilding%20teams%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20talented%20people%2C%20but%20it%20wasn't%20all%20roses.%20Rapid%20changes%20and%20looming%20crises%20were%20constants%2C%20as%20they%20seem%20to%20be%20at%20most%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20I%20was%20working%20at%20Airbnb%20when%20COVID-19%20hit%20in%202020.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffinance.yahoo.com%2Fnews%2Fairbnb-lost-80-business-march-105004047.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20company%20lost%2080%25%20of%20its%20business%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20matter%20of%20weeks%2C%20and%20by%20May%2C%20I%20was%20forced%20to%20lay%20off%20more%20than%2025%25%20of%20my%20team.%20Managing%20that%20crisis%20and%20recovery%20was%20one%20of%20the%20most%20difficult%20leadership%20crucibles%20of%20my%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20everyday%20chaos%20of%20a%20fast-paced%20company%20was%20just%20as%20educational%2C%20though%2C%20and%20one%20strategy%20for%20managing%20it%20rose%20above%20the%20rest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftop-3-traits-of-effective-leaders-2015-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esecret%20to%20effective%20leadership%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20times%20of%20change%20%E2%80%94%20whether%20it's%20reorgs%2C%20strategy%20shifts%2C%20or%20layoffs%20%E2%80%94%20is%20to%20provide%20authentic%20clarity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClarity%20allows%20people%20to%20move%20forward%20calmly%2C%20even%20if%20they%20don't%20have%20all%20the%20answers.%20In%20a%20chaotic%20environment%2C%20providing%20clarity%20takes%20frequent%20communication%20in%20an%20authentic%20voice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222b88c995-bc41-4177-a9e8-f28ad92b19cc%5C%22%3EClarity%2C%20not%20certainty%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEarly%20in%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-tech-career-progression-soft-skills-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eleadership%20career%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20I%20mistakenly%20assumed%20that%20being%20a%20decisive%20leader%20in%20a%20crisis%20meant%20projecting%20certainty.%20My%20logic%20was%20that%20people%20need%20to%20be%20reassured%20their%20leader%20knows%20exactly%20what%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20quickly%20realized%20that%20was%20a%20fantasy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20can't%20remember%20a%20single%20time%20in%20my%20leadership%20career%20when%20I%20had%20all%20the%20answers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%2C%20in%20an%20effort%20to%20project%20certainty%2C%20I%20confidently%20presented%20some%20details%20using%20guesswork.%20But%20things%20were%20moving%20fast%2C%20and%20the%20information%20I%20shared%20was%20proven%20wrong%20just%20days%20later.%20What%20I%20thought%20would%20be%20useful%20only%20made%20me%20look%20foolish%20and%20ultimately%20damaged%20my%20team's%20trust%20in%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20few%20failed%20efforts%2C%20I%20realized%20my%20team%20didn't%20need%20me%20to%20have%20all%20the%20answers%3B%20they%20just%20needed%20me%20to%20provide%20clarity%20about%20what%20was%20happening.%20I%20learned%20the%20importance%20of%20clarity%20in%20three%20key%20areas%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Col%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20happening%3F%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIt's%20essential%20to%20clearly%20state%20the%20facts%20as%20you%20know%20them%2C%20even%20if%20they're%20incomplete%2C%20to%20help%20people%20process%20what's%20happening.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Fol%3E%3Col%20start%3D%5C%222%5C%22%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20is%20it%20happening%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Sharing%20the%20%26quot%3Bwhat%26quot%3B%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewithout%20the%20%26quot%3Bwhy%26quot%3B%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3Eis%20a%20key%20mistake.%20My%20understanding%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bwhy%26quot%3B%20was%20usually%20incomplete%2C%20but%20sharing%20any%20context%20I%20had%20helped%20my%20teams%20make%20sense%20of%20it.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Fol%3E%3Col%20start%3D%5C%223%5C%22%3E%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20does%20it%20mean%20for%20me%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20It's%20usually%20hard%20for%20people%20to%20translate%20high-level%20changes%20down%20to%20their%20level.%20Even%20simple%20reminders%20like%20%26quot%3BYour%20day-to-day%20work%20won't%20change%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BHere's%20when%20we'll%20know%20how%20this%20will%20affect%20our%20road%20map%2C%26quot%3B%20helped%20people%20feel%20calmer.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Fol%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcomparably-large-companies-highly-rated-leadership-teams-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebest%20leaders%3C%2Fa%3E%20I've%20worked%20with%20were%20proactive%20about%20answering%20these%20questions%2C%20reaching%20out%20to%20teams%20early%20and%20often.%20I%20made%20it%20a%20practice%20to%20hold%20frequent%20Q%26amp%3BA%20sessions%20with%20my%20teams%2C%20and%20say%20things%20like%3A%20%26quot%3BGood%20question%2C%20I%20don't%20know.%20Let%20me%20see%20