dwcdn.net%2Fzefjq%2Ffull.png%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flsa.umich.edu%2Fsoc%2Fpeople%2Ffaculty%2Fpjsmock.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPamela%20Smock%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20sociology%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Michigan%2C%20said%20having%20two%20kids%20has%20been%20an%20American%20ideal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.statista.com%2Fstatistics%2F718084%2Faverage-number-of-own-children-per-family%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esince%20the%201960s%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20difference%20between%20the%20generations%20is%20that%20millennials%20are%20less%20likely%20to%20have%20kids%20than%20previous%20generations.%20In%20that%20sense%2C%20a%20young%20family%20with%20two%20kids%20is%20no%20longer%20the%20norm%2C%20but%2C%20for%20some%2C%20a%20symbol%20of%20luxury.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20see%20marriage%20and%20childbearing%20as%20something%20to%20do%20once%20they%20feel%20economically%20comfortable%2C%26quot%3B%20Smock%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20many%2C%20that%20means%20not%20having%20any%20debt%20and%20being%20able%20to%20afford%20a%20mortgage.%20The%20average%20millennial%20borrower%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bankrate.com%2Floans%2Fstudent-loans%2Fstudent-loan-debt-by-generation%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eowes%20%2442%2C000%20in%20student%20loan%20debt%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20part%20of%20why%20it's%20so%20difficult%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-cant-millennials-buy-homes-first-time-buyers-mortgage-rates-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emillennials%20to%20buy%20their%20first%20homes%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Comparatively%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconreview.studentorg.berkeley.edu%2Fbaby-boomers-and-the-future-of-homeownership-in-the-united-states%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E45%25%20of%20baby%20boomers%3C%2Fa%3E%20bought%20their%20first%20homes%20between%20the%20ages%20of%202