%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20new%20kind%20of%20dealmaking%20sweeping%20Silicon%20Valley%20is%20dividing%20employees%20into%20haves%20and%20have-nots.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EInvestors%20and%20founders%20say%20it%20is%20more%20important%20than%20ever%20for%20job%20candidates%20to%20do%20careful%20diligence.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20most%20crucial%20thing%20to%20assess%20is%20how%20much%20you%20trust%20the%20founder%2C%20multiple%20investors%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20new%20kind%20of%20dealmaking%20is%20sweeping%20Silicon%20Valley%2C%20forcing%20employees%20to%20be%20vigilant%20about%20how%20much%20trust%20they%20are%20willing%20to%20put%20in%20startup%20founders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20two%20years%2C%20instead%20of%20acquiring%20AI%20startups%20outright%2C%20Big%20Tech%20companies%20have%20been%20licensing%20their%20technology%20or%20making%20deals%20for%20top%20talent%2C%20with%20startup%20employees%20sometimes%20getting%20divided%20into%20separate%20camps%20of%20haves%20and%20have-nots.%20Those%20with%20the%20most%20desirable%20AI%20skills%20reap%20a%20windfall%20while%20those%20who%20remain%20are%20shrouded%20in%20uncertainty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20recently%20happened%20to%20Windsurf%20employees%20after%20the%20AI%20coding%20company%20was%20on%20the%20verge%20of%20being%20acquired%20by%20OpenAI%20for%20%243%20billion%2C%20but%20was%20instead%20split%20in%20half.%20Google%20paid%20billions%20to%20hire%20Windsurf's%20CEO%20and%20top%20talent%2C%20and%20the%20hundreds%20of%20employees%20who%20remained%20were%20bought%20by%20another%20startup%2C%20Cognition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%20for%20startup%20employees%2C%20many%20investors%20expect%20these%20kinds%20of%20novel%20transactions%20to%20continue%20as%20the%20velocity%20of%20developments%20in%20AI%20makes%20companies%20unlikely%20to%20want%20to%20wait%20months%20or%20years%20for%20regulatory%20approval.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226d9f7b75-5ab5-4429-a4b5-9711f40803fc%5C%22%3ECandidates%20need%20to%20ask%20tough%20questions%20about%20the%20founder%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20traditional%20M%26amp%3BA%20has%20mostly%20gone%20out%20the%20window%2C%20it%20is%20more%20important%20than%20ever%20for%20startup%20employees%20to%20do%20their%20homework%2C%20advises%20Steve%20Brotman%2C%20managing%20partner%20at%20Alpha%20Partners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20light%20of%20what%20we%20just%20saw%20with%20Windsurf%2C%20it's%20crucial%20to%20understand%20the%20ownership%20dynamics%2C%26quot%3B%20Brotman%20said.%20%26quot%3B%20You%20don't%20want%20to%20be%20working%20100-hour%20weeks%20only%20to%20realize%20your%20options%20are%20underwater%20or%20your%20exit%20upside%20is%20capped.%20And%20remember%3A%20companies%20that%20are%20transparent%20and%20deliberate%20about%20governance%20tend%20to%20be%20better%20long-term%20bets%2C%20both%20for%20your%20career%20and%20your%20equity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAsk%20hard%20questions%20about%20runway%2C%20revenue%2C%20burn%2C%20and%20investor%20syndicate%20quality%2C%26quot%3B%20Brotman%20continued.%20%26quot%3BWho's%20on%20the%20board%3F%20Are%20they%20structured%20for%20long-term%20growth%20or%20a%20quick%20flip%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20important%20thing%20candidates%20should%20assess%20is%20how%20much%20they%20trust%20the%20founder%2C%20according%20to%20Deedy%20Das%2C%20an%20investor%20at%20Menlo%20Ventures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNobody%20wants%20to%20talk%20about%20the%20fact%20that%20founders%20control%20almost%20everything%20that%20happens%20in%20a%20company%2C%20including%20how%20you%20get%20paid%2C%20when%20you%20get%20paid%2C%20how%20the%20equity%20vests%2C%20and%20when%20you%20can%20sell%20the%20equity%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Das.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20everything%2C%20so%20having%20trust%20in%20your%20founder%20to%20do%20the%20right%20thing%20by%20the%20team%20is%20extremely%20important.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20as%20investors%20would%20typically%20r