ESeeing%20the%20problem%20beneath%20the%20surface%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESushmita%E2%80%99s%20interest%20in%20ecology%20began%20early.%20Through%20her%20life%20sciences%20education%2C%20she%20found%20herself%20drawn%20to%20the%20complex%20relationships%20between%20species%20and%20ecosystems.%20But%20it%20was%20during%20her%20internship%20at%20the%20Indian%20Institute%20of%20Science%20in%202021%20that%20something%20shifted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20was%20working%20on%20insect%20pests%20and%20the%20economic%20losses%20they%20caused.%20That%E2%80%99s%20when%20I%20first%20started%20looking%20closely%20at%20invasive%20species%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20recalls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-media-text%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-media-text__content%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20such%20species%20was%20water%20hyacinth.%20While%20some%20researchers%20praised%20its%20ability%20to%20purify%20water%20by%20absorbing%20heavy%20metals%2C%20others%20raised%20concerns%20about%20its%20impact%20on%20native%20biodiversity.%20The%20conflicting%20opinions%20intrigued%20her%20%E2%80%94%20and%20left%20her%20with%20more%20questions%20than%20answers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWater%20hyacinth%20has%20two%20faces%2C%20even%20in%20research%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%20%E2%80%9CTechnologists%20see%20it%20as%20a%20boon%20because%20it%20phytoremediates%20water.%20But%20ecologists%20see%20it%20as%20a%20threat.%20It%20spreads%20fast%20and%20suffocates%20everything%20else.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20places%20like%20Karnataka%2C%20it%20was%20even%20introduced%20deliberately%2C%20with%20the%20hope%20that%20it%20would%20help%20clean%20polluted%20water%20bodies.%20But%20its%20rapid%20multiplication%20soon%20made%20it%20unmanageable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-media-text__media%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%20500px)%20100vw%2C%20500px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan-3_11zon-1753266935-500x664.jpeg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan-3_11zon-1753266935-500x664.jpeg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan-3_11zon-1753266935-226x300.jpeg%20226w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan-3_11zon-1753266935-768x1020.jpeg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan-3_11zon-1753266935-1156x1536.jpeg%201156w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan-3_11zon-1753266935-1542x2048.jpeg%201542w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan-3_11zon-1753266935-150x199.jpeg%20150w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan-3_11zon-1753266935-1200x1594.jpeg%201200w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-475013%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22664%5C%22%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20in%20states%20like%20Assam%20and%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20small%20communities%20had%20begun%20using%20water%20hyacinth%20to%20make%20crafts%20like%20baskets%20and%20bags.%20But%20these%20efforts%2C%20while%20creative%2C%20weren%E2%80%99t%20easy%20to%20scale.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20time-consuming%20work%2C%20and%20people%20weren%E2%80%99t%20buying%20those%20products%20in%20large%20numbers%2C%E2%80%9D%20Sushmita%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EThe%20plant%20that%20refuses%20to%20die%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20didn%E2%80%99t%20take%20long%20for%20Sushmita%20to%20realise%20that%20water%20hyacinth%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20just%20a%20local%20nuisance%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20a%20large-scale%20ecological%20crisis.%20What%20makes%20it%20so%20difficult%20to%20control%20is%20its%20extraordinary%20ability%20to%20multiply.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-media-text%5C%22%3E%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-media-text__media%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%20473px)%20100vw%2C%20473px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan-5_11zon-1753267025-473x1024.jpeg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22473%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan-5_11zon-1753267025-473x1024.jpeg%20473w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan-5_11zon-1753267025-139x300.jpeg%20139w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan-5_11zon-1753267025-709x1536.jpeg%20709w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan-5_11zon-1753267025-150x325.jpeg%20150w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan-5_11zon-1753267025.jpeg%20739w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-475015%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-media-text__content%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COne%20water%20hyacinth%20plant%20can%20produce%20around%203%2C000%20seeds%20in%20its%20lifetime%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20explains.%20%E2%80%9CAnd%20those%20seeds%20can%20stay%20dormant%20for%20up%20to%2020%20years%20if%20the%20conditions%20aren%E2%80%99t%20right.%20Once%20they%20find%20the%20right%20conditions%2C%20they%20grow%20back%20within%207%20to%2014%20days.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20result%20is%20a%20dense%2C%20fast-spreading%20carpet%20that%20clogs%20waterways%2C%20depletes%20oxygen%2C%20and%20threatens%20aquatic%20ecosystems.%20In%20Trichy%20alone%2C%20the%20plant%20covers%20nearly%2021%20km%20of%20water%20bodies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20monsoon%20each%20year%2C%20the%20government%20attempts%20to%20clear%20some%20of%20this%20biomass%20%E2%80%94%20but%20the%20efforts%20barely%20make%20a%20dent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThey%20manage%20to%20clear%20just%202%20km%20before%20the%20rains%20begin%2C%E2%80%9D%20Sushmita%20says.%20%E2%80%9CAnd%20even%20that%20takes%20a%20bulldozer%2C%20several%20days%2C%20and%20about%2020%20lorry%20loads%20of%20hyacinth.%20It%E2%80%99s%20expensive%2C%20time-consuming%2C%20and%20all%20of%20it%20ends%20up%20in%20landfills.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%20500px)%20100vw%2C%20500px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan-6_11zon-1753267107-500x333.jpeg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Sushmita%E2%80%99s%20sessions%20combine%20science%20with%20hands-on%20learning%20to%20rethink%20invasive%20species%20as%20resources.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan-6_11zon-1753267107-500x333.jpeg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan-6_11zon-1753267107-300x200.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan-6_11zon-1753267107-768x512.jpeg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan-6_11zon-1753267107-1536x1023.jpeg%201536w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan-6_11zon-1753267107-1200x800.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan-6_11zon-1753267107-150x100.jpeg%20150w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan-6_11zon-1753267107.jpeg%201600w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-475018%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ESushmita%E2%80%99s%20sessions%20combine%20science%20with%20hands-on%20learning%20to%20rethink%20invasive%20species%20as%20resources.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEvery%20year%2C%20the%20cycle%20repeats%20%E2%80%94%20draining%20public%20funds%20while%20offering%20no%20lasting%20solution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EA%20breakthrough%20in%20Germany%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202024%2C%20Sushmita%E2%80%99s%20search%20for%20a%20better%20solution%20led%20her%20far%20from%20Tamil%20Nadu%20%E2%80%94%20to%20the%20labs%20of%20the%20University%20of%20Hamburg%20in%20Germany.%20She%20had%20been%20selected%20for%20the%20prestigious%20International%20Sustainability%20Academy%20(ISA)%20fellowship%2C%20which%20supports%20young%20changemakers%20tackling%20global%20environmental%20challenges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOut%20of%20hundreds%20of%20applicants%2C%20she%20was%20one%20of%20only%2012%20fellows%20chosen%20worldwide%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20only%20one%20from%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan_11zon-1753267363.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Sushmita%E2%80%99s%20workshops%20teach%20how%201%20kg%20of%20water%20hyacinth%20can%20be%20turned%20into%2030%20sheets%20of%20paper.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan_11zon-1753267363.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan_11zon-1753267363-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan_11zon-1753267363-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan_11zon-1753267363-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FSushmita-Krishnan_11zon-1753267363-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-475020%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ESushmita%E2%80%99s%20workshops%20teach%20how%201%20kg%20of%20water%20hyacinth%20can%20be%20turned%20into%2030%20sheets%20of%20paper.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAt%20the%20University%20of%20Hamburg%2C%20I%20worked%20in%20a%20wood%20chemistry%20lab%20with%20Professor%20Bodosake%2C%20who%20specialises%20in%20pulp-making%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20recalls.%20%E2%80%9CThat%E2%80%99s%20where%20we%20began%20experimenting%20with%20water%20hyacinth%20as%20a%20paper%20raw%20material.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20results%20surprised%20even%20the%20researchers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNormally%2C%20making%20paper%20from%20wood%20pulp%20uses%20around%2060%25%20soda.%20But%20we%20found%20that%20with%20water%20hyacinth%2C%20you%20only%20need%20about%206%25.%20And%20the%20quality%20of%20the%20pulp%20was%20excellent%20%E2%80%94%20strong%2C%20clean%2C%20and%20easy%20to%20work%20with.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20breakthrough%20proved%20what%20she%20had%20long%20suspected%20%E2%80%94%20water%20hyacinth%20didn%E2%80%99t%20need%20to%20be%20a%20burden.%20With%20the%20right%20technique%2C%20it%20could%20become%20a%20sustainable%2C%20scalable%20material.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EBack%20home%2C%20but%20not%20yet%20on%20board%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEnergised%20by%20her%20success%20in%20Germany%2C%20Sushmita%20returned%20to%20India%20with%20a%20clear%20goal%20%E2%80%94%20to%20scale%20up%20the%20process%20and%20introduce%20water%20hyacinth%20paper%20into%20mainstream%20production.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-media-text%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-media-text__content%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20began%20reaching%20out%20to%20paper%20industries%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20could%20be%20a%20new%20income%20source%